f(x,g) = g x
g is a callback

it equals to f(x)(g), still callback

bind instead of map?

https://philipnilsson.github.io/Badness10k/escaping-hell-with-monads/

var a = getData();
if (a != null) {
  var b = getMoreData(a);
  if (b != null) {
     var c = getMoreData(b);
     if (c != null) {
        var d = getEvenMoreData(a, c)
        if (d != null) {
          print(d);
        }
     }
  }
}

Ad hoc solution: Elvis operators
var a = getData();
var b = a?.getMoreData();
var c = b?.getMoreData();
var d = c?.getEvenMoreData(a);
print(d);

Maybe monad 

do
  a <- getData
  b <- getMoreData a
  c <- getMoreData b
  d <- getEvenMoreData a c
  print d


